{% extends "layout.html" %}

{% block content %}
<div class="jumbotron text-center">
  <div class="container">
    <a href="/" class="lang-logo">
      <img src="/images/lang-logo.png">
    </a>
    <h1>Getting Started with PHP on Dokku</h1>
    <p>This is a sample PHP application deployed to Dokku. It's a reasonably simple app - but a good foundation for understanding how to get the most out of the Dokku platform.</p>
    <a type="button" class="btn btn-lg btn-default" href="https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-php"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flash"></span> Getting Started with PHP</a>
    <a type="button" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary" href="https://github.com/heroku/php-getting-started"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-download"></span> Source on GitHub</a>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="container">
  <div class="alert alert-info text-center" role="alert">
    To deploy your own copy, and learn the fundamentals of the Dokku platform, head over to the <a href="https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-php" class="alert-link">Getting Started with PHP on Dokku</a> tutorial.
  </div>
  <hr>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">
      <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span> How this sample app works</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>This app was deployed to Dokku, either using Git or by using <a href="https://github.com/heroku/php-getting-started">Dokku Button</a> on the repository.</li>

        <li>When Dokku received the source code, it grabbed all the dependencies in the <a href="https://github.com/heroku/php-getting-started/blob/master/composer.json">composer.json</a>.</li>
        <li>The platform then spins up a dyno, a lightweight container that provides an isolated environment in which the slug can be mounted and executed.</li>
        <li>You can scale your app, manage it, and deploy over <a href="https://addons.heroku.com/">150 add-on services</a>, from the Dashboard or CLI.</li>
        <li>Check out the <a href="https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-php">Getting Started</a> guide to learn more!</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
      <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-link"></span> Helpful Links</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.heroku.com/home">Dokku</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://devcenter.heroku.com/">Dokku Dev Center</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-php">Getting Started with PHP on Dokku</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/deploying-php">Deploying PHP Apps on Dokku</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div> <!-- row -->
   <div class="alert alert-info text-center" role="alert">
    Please do work through the Getting Started guide, even if you do know how to build such an application.  The guide covers the basics of working with Dokku, and will familiarize you with all the concepts you need in order to build and deploy your own apps.
  </div>
</div>

{% endblock %}
